detailed_results.sentence: Security - This term relates to the safety and protection of individuals, assets, or information from harm, theft, loss, or unauthorized access.
Migration - Refers to the movement of people across regions or countries, often in search of better opportunities, fleeing conflict, or due to environmental factors.
Couch - A piece of furniture designed for seating multiple people, typically placed in living rooms.
Prescription - A written order by a healthcare provider that authorizes a patient to receive certain medications.
Hardly - An adverb indicating something is barely the case or only just happening.
Existence - The state of being real or actual; having life, substance, or reality.
Hear - To perceive sound with one's ears.
System - A set of connected things or parts forming a complex whole, usually organized in a particular way to function effectively.
Characteristic - A feature or quality that is typical of or serves to distinguish something or someone.
Purpose - The reason for which something is done, created, or exists; the goal it is intended to achieve.
Travel - To make a journey, typically by going from one place to another, often over long distances.
Development - The process of growth, improvement, or expansion in an individual, country, technology, etc.
Guarantee - A promise or assurance that something will happen or be done as stated; sometimes involves compensation if the promise is not fulfilled.
Level-up - An increase or progress to a higher level, often used in gaming contexts but can also apply to personal growth or career advancement.
Software - Programs and other operating information used by computers and digital devices for various tasks.
Draft - A preliminary version of a document, bill, or law that is subject to further consideration and revision before final adoption.
Above - In or to a higher place; situated at or extending toward the top or over something.
Order - To arrange or command in an authoritative manner; also refers to a sequence or systematized structure.
Pleasure - A feeling of happy satisfaction and enjoyment, often derived from activities one enjoys.
Deadline - The latest time or date by which something must be completed or submitted.
